Author: scifichick774<br>
Rating: PG-13<br>
Category: Humor/Romance/Angst<br>
Spoilers: Up through Rosetta in the second season, but with no Helen (as it should be).<br>
Summary: Valentine’s Day fic challenge.  Lucas wants to know why all the girls in Smallville like Clark.  Chloe/Lex<br>
Disclaimer: Not mine, no infringement intended, please don’t sue.<br>
Feedback: YES!! REVIEW!!  Geez, that sounded incredibly needy.<br>
Archival: Sure – just let me know where.<br>
Author’s Note:  Response to Jaimie’s fic challenge.  Requirements are as follows: Chloe/Lex with moderate Lucas/Chloe pining, mention of Stargate SG-1’s Teal’c, chocolate covered coffee beans and mocha truffles, song lyrics to A-HA’s “You’ll Never Get Over Me”, and all this within 3 chapters or less.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Lucas leaned against the wall of the Talon as he watched Lana smile sweetly at Clark.  He shook his head.  <br>
<br>
“What is it with the girls in this town?  You put on some flannel and suddenly you’re attractive?”  Lucas asked.  Lex grinned from his seat at the table next to his brother.<br>
<br>
“You could try it and find out,” he said snidely.  Lucas tilted his head at him and gave him a ‘thanks, but no thanks’ look.  Lex smiled and glanced over at the counter Lucas had just been staring at.  “Ah.  You like Lana,” he observed.  Lucas shrugged as if it were nothing.<br>
<br>
“No,” he said.  “She’s a little too cow-town for my tastes.”  Lex just grinned at his brother and took a sip of his coffee.  “But see?  Look, here comes that cute little blonde girl and she’s going to hang all over him too.”  Lex followed Lucas’s gaze to the front door and saw Chloe walking in.  Lex furrowed his brow and turned back to look at Lucas, who was still watching Chloe.<br>
<br>
“You like Chloe?”  Lex asked in surprise.<br>
<br>
“I didn’t say that,” Lucas said.  “I was just pointing out that all the girls here seem to go for your friend, the farm boy.”<br>
<br>
“Uh huh,” Lex said unconvinced, especially since he noticed that Lucas still had his eyes focused on Chloe.  Lucas looked over at Lex with Lex’s comment and pushed himself off the wall.  He took a seat across from his brother.<br>
<br>
“Okay, so say I like a chick here in town; you think I should wear flannel and that will make her notice me?”  Lucas asked skeptically.<br>
<br>
“I think if you call Miss Sullivan a *chick* that she’s likely to deck you,” Lex answered.  Lucas smiled.<br>
<br>
“Fiery,” he said in an impressed tone.  “I can handle that.”  <br>
<br>
“No you can’t,” Lex said dryly.  Lucas leaned forward.<br>
<br>
“You know the women here so well?”  Lucas asked.  “Tell me the way to her heart.”<br>
<br>
“I would if I thought it was her heart you were interested in,” Lex said with a small smirk.  <br>
<br>
“You’re a laugh a minute,” Lucas said sarcastically.  Lex’s smirk turned into a broad smile.<br>
<br>
“If you like her, why don’t you just ask her out?”  Lex asked.  He already knew the reason, but his brother had been a major pain in the ass since he came back to town, and he was going to have some fun with this.  Lucas glanced back at the counter, where Chloe and Lana were both talking to Clark.  He looked back at Lex.<br>
<br>
“Number one, I didn’t say I liked her.”  He looked back over at Chloe for a second.  “But she could be a nice diversion,” he mused aloud.  Lex arched a disapproving eyebrow.  “And second, you *know* why,” he said.  “Because your *brother* Clark hates me and will kill me if I get anywhere near one of his women.”  Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Not true,” Lex said and took another sip of his coffee.  “He’ll probably just maim you.”  Lucas rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
“Fine.  You’re not going to help me?  I know how to get her attention.”<br>
<br>
“Oh, really?  You’re going to try and impress her with your vast knowledge of Edge City’s underworld?”  Lex asked sarcastically.  “Or maybe tell her how you’re going to become a corporate giant in a few years.”<br>
<br>
“Depends,” Lucas said.  “Did it work for you?”<br>
<br>
“No.”<br>
<br>
“Well, I guess I won’t be using that then – even though it would probably work for me since I’m better looking,” Lucas said with a smug smile.  Lex laughed and Lucas stood up.<br>
<br>
“So, what are you going to do?”<br>
<br>
“Watch and find out,” Lucas said, turning his back to Lex.  Lex shook his head.<br>
<br>
‘He’s going to get decked – and he’s going to deserve it,’ Lex thought with a smile.<br>
<br>
Lucas strolled over to the counter where Clark was now only talking to Chloe, as Lana was waiting on a table.  Clark eyed him skeptically.<br>
<br>
“Hey Clark,” Lucas said and patted the back of his shoulder.  “You going to introduce me to your friend?”<br>
<br>
“I wasn’t planning to,” Clark replied with a forced smile.  Chloe laughed and stuck her hand out.<br>
<br>
“Chloe Sullivan,” she greeted.  “You’re Lex’s brother, right?”  He nodded and shook her hand.<br>
<br>
“Lucas Luthor,” he said.  Clark arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“You took the last name?”<br>
<br>
“Well,” Lucas said as he shoved his hands into his pockets, “having the Luthor name comes with certain advantages.”<br>
<br>
“I’ll bet,” Chloe said.  Lucas leaned toward her in a leering fashion and Lex frowned as he watched his brother try to pick up on Chloe.  Granted, he didn’t know her that well, but he didn’t like the way he felt when Lucas mentioned that he liked her; and felt even worse when Lucas said something about her being a ‘diversion’. <br>
<br>
‘And yet, you didn’t feel at all threatened when you thought he liked Lana,’ his inner voice said.  Lex frowned again and pushed himself away from the table.  He grabbed his cup and started to walk toward the counter.  He motioned to the waitress behind the counter for a refill with his mug and turned to face Clark, Lucas, and Chloe.<br>
<br>
“I thought you said you weren’t going to help me?”  Lucas asked.  <br>
<br>
“Just getting a refill,” Lex replied.  Lucas nodded and Clark narrowed his eyes at him.<br>
<br>
“Help you with what?”  Clark asked suspiciously.  Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“Good question Clark.  I’ll make a reporter out of you yet,” she said.  Lex smiled at her response, but Clark and Lucas kept their eyes fixed on each other in what looked like a staring contest.<br>
<br>
“Well, Valentine’s Day is tomorrow,” Lucas started as he looked back over at Chloe.  Chloe rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, great,” she mumbled.<br>
<br>
“You don’t like Valentine’s Day?”  Lex asked.  Lucas creased his brow.<br>
<br>
“I thought all chicks liked Valentine’s Day,” he said.  Chloe stared at him in disbelief.<br>
<br>
“Did you just call me a *chick*?”  She asked.  Lex and Clark both smiled.  Lex slapped his brother’s back.<br>
<br>
“And here’s the part where you get hurt,” he said cheerfully.  Lucas rolled his eyes and didn’t see Chloe grab Lex’s new mug of coffee off of the counter.  She threw the contents of the cup toward Lucas and he yelped as the hot liquid splashed on him.  Chloe got her bag and walked out of the Talon, waving politely to Lana as she left.  Lex and Clark both started laughing heartily while Lucas looked down at his wet shirt and jacket.<br>
<br>
“Damn it!”<br>
<br>
“You completely deserved it,” Lex said.  Lucas nodded.<br>
<br>
“You’re right,” he said.  Both Lex and Clark seemed stunned to hear him admit it.  Lucas looked over toward Lana.  “I should have gone for the brunette.”<br>
