<br>
“I wanted to apologize for my brother and the incident yesterday.”<br>
<br>
“Not necessary,” she said.  Lex tilted his head at her as she started typing again.  He walked closer to her and she finally looked up at him again when he half-sat on the edge of her desk.  “Was there something else?”<br>
<br>
“Why do you hate Valentine’s Day?”<br>
<br>
“What?”<br>
<br>
“Why do you hate Valentine’s Day?”  He repeated.  <br>
<br>
“I – I don’t *hate* it,” she answered.  “I just don’t like it.”<br>
